  "prompt": "Is morning sickness a sign of good pregnancy?",
  "response": "Morning sickness, which includes nausea and vomiting during pregnancy, is a common symptom experienced by many pregnant women, particularly in the first trimester. While it is uncomfortable, it is often viewed as a positive sign in terms of pregnancy health. \n\nResearch suggests that morning sickness may be associated with a healthy pregnancy and a lower risk of miscarriage. This is because it is believed to be linked to higher levels of hormones such as human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG) and estrogen, which are crucial for maintaining pregnancy. \n\nHowever, it's important to note that the absence of morning sickness is not necessarily a bad sign. Many women have healthy pregnancies without experiencing significant nausea or vomiting. Each pregnancy is unique, and symptoms can vary widely from one person to another.\n\nIf morning sickness is severe or if you have concerns about your symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare provider. Severe morning sickness, known as hyperemesis gravidarum, may require medical attention to ensure both the mother's and baby's health is maintained.",
